Brazilian Stock Movers: Lojas Renner, LLX Logistica, Petrobras

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-08-29T20:54:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/brazil-stock-movers-lojas-renner-llx-logistica-petrobras.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 2.8 percent to 54,860.73.  Lojas Renner SA (LREN3 BS),  Brazil ’s biggest publicly-
traded clothing retailer, gained 4 percent to 58.25 reais, its
highest price in almost seven weeks, on speculation Brazil will
announce spending cuts, which may compel the central bank to
reduce borrowing costs. Lojas Renner led gains for companies
that depend on consumer demand.  LLX Logistica SA (LLXL3)  (LLXL3 BS), the port company controlled by
Brazilian billionaire  Eike Batista , advanced 5.7 percent to 3.92
reais as Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  announced the government
would increase its primary surplus target and as economists
forecast lower borrowing costs in Brazil in 2012.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  (PETR4 BS), Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company, increased 3 percent to 20.49 reais as
crude for October delivery advanced 2.2 percent to settle at
$87.27 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange  after a
report that U.S. consumer spending rose in July, boosting
optimism that the world’s largest economy will continue to
expand.  PDG Realty SA Empreendimentos & Participacoes (PDGR3 BS),
Brazil’s biggest homebuilder by revenue, surged 7.9 percent, the
most in three weeks, to 7.22 reais as expectations for lower
 interest rates  boosted homebuilders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
